<HEAD>West Germans Are World's Biggest Fruit Juice Consumers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 West Germans may be the world's greatest beer lovers, but now they're tops in fruit juice consumption, too According to the Bonn-based <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> German </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fruit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Juice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION>, West Germans drank 33.5 quarts of fruit juice per capita in 1987. This represents an 11-percent increase over 1986 and is the highest worldwide. In second place in national juice consumption is neighboring <LOCATION> Switzerland </LOCATION>. In 1987, the average Swiss drank 29.6 quarts. Fruit juice drinking in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> was given as 27.6 quarts per capita. The West German fruit juice industry had around $ 1.65 billion in sales last year, the association reported.
