with quotes from PRI officials. PICKS up 9th graf, `This year .. .'
EDITS to conform.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By ISAAC A. LEVI</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Opposition candidates accused the government of fraud in presidential elections Wednesday and met jointly with federal officials to protest. A journalist reported that an 8-year-old boy voted in one town. There appeared to be little doubt, however, that <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Salinas </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Gortari </PERSON> of the governing <ORGANIZATION> Institutional </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revolutionary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, would win a six-year term as president in an unbroken tradition dating to 1929. Official returns were not expected before Sunday. <PERSON> Salinas </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Gortari </PERSON>'s most visible opponent, <PERSON> Cuauhtemoc </PERSON> <PERSON> Cardenas </PERSON> of the leftist coalition <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION>, told a news conference the government `` is intending to have a fraud.'' `` We have begun to receive information nationwide that is not favorable for the government party,'' he said, before leaving for his meeting with <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Clouthier </PERSON> of the conservative <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Action </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Rosario </PERSON> <PERSON> Ibarra </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Piedra </PERSON> of the radical <ORGANIZATION> Revolutionary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>. The three scheduled a news conference after their meeting with <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Bartlett </PERSON>. `` I want to tell you that all of these irregular acts, all of these repeated acts throughout the country, have created a situation of irregularity,'' <PERSON> Cardenas </PERSON> said. The party in power, known as the <ORGA