nd landers to reach Phobos, and then will begin to track the <LOCATION> Martian </LOCATION> moon precisely using antennas in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>, and a Soviet radio telescope in the <LOCATION> Crimea </LOCATION>.
