ne mile deep at the point when the <ORGANIZATION> Airbus </ORGANIZATION> was nine miles away, the point at which the Vicennes fired SM-2 Standard missiles at it and knocked it down. It would have been almost impossible for any other aircraft to have been within that area, he said. The plane was mistaken for an F-14, <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> said, because the <ORGANIZATION> Airbus </ORGANIZATION> was transmitting an identification signal on a frequency normally reserved for military aircraft. <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> also said that <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> should share some responsibility for the downing of the plane because it took off from the joint military and civilian airfield at <PERSON> Bandar </PERSON> <PERSON> Abbas </PERSON> during an exchange of fire between the <LOCATION> Vincennes </LOCATION> and Iranian gunboats and was headed straight at the <LOCATION> Vincennes </LOCATION> when it was shot down. `` The Iranians are the ones who bear the resonsibility for ensuring that if they are the ones who provoke the hostilities, they are the ones who began the shooting in this incident, that they ensure the safety of their civilian aircraft by not sending them into harm's way,'' <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> said.
