N> Wallach </PERSON>'s behest, on behalf of a $ 1 billion proposed <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> oil pipeline project in 1985 <PERSON> McKay </PERSON> reviewed the attorney general's meetings with and decision on behalf of executives of the regional <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> telephone companies at a time when he held $ 14,000 in telephone stock. The independent counsel also looked into the fact that members of a <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> real estate family, through a foundation, arranged to pay a $ 40,000-a-year salary for <PERSON> Meese </PERSON>'s wife while leasing office space to the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Wallach </PERSON> was involved with <PERSON> Meese </PERSON> in both the phone stock and Mrs. <PERSON> Meese </PERSON>'s job.
