<HEAD>GE's Earnings Up 23 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday said its second quarter profit jumped 16 percent because of strong performances by the company's plastics, broadcasting and financial services operations. The Fairfield-based company said net earnings totaled $ 835 million, or 93 cents a share, up from $ 720 million, or 79 cents a share originally reported for the the same period a year ago. <ORGANIZATION> GE </ORGANIZATION>'s 1987 quarterly earnings were restated at year-end to reflect adoption of new income tax accounting rules. The company said in a statement that ongoing operations are not affected by the change. Sales during the second quarter totaled $ 9.25 billion, off 3 percent from $ 9.56 billion in the previous quarter when sales of the company's consumer electronics businesses were included. GE-RCA Consumer Electronics, which contributed about $ 3 billion a year in sales, was sold to <ORGANIZATION> Thomson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> SA </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> late last year. `` With these results, <ORGANIZATION> GE </ORGANIZATION> is well on its way to a second consecutive full year of strong double-digit increases in earnings,'' said <ORGANIZATION> GE </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Welch </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>. <PERSON> Welch </PERSON> also said that since the last earnings report, the company has forged several important agreements, one with labor and two to expand the plastics business On Wednesday, <ORGANIZATION> GE </ORGANIZATION>'s largest union, the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electronic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION>, overwhelmingly ratified a new three-year national contract. GE Plastics formed a joint venture with <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Carbide </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s silicone business GE also signed a definitive agreement to <ORGANIZATION> Borg-Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s chemical businesses for about $ 2.3 billion. The company said <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s television operations posted solid improvements in profits, while revenue held at last year's levels. Earnings for the first six months of 1988 were $ 1.56 billion, or $ 1.73 a share, up 16 percent from $ 1.34 billion, or $ 1.47 a share in the first half of last year. Sales during the period totaled $ 17.22 billion, down 4 percent from $ 17.86 billion in the year-ago period, which included the consumer electronics operations.
