firm who made large donations to both the <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> Socialist parties were arrested for evading income taxes of $ 12 million, earned from illegal stocks manipulation. Former Prime Minister <PERSON> Kakuei </PERSON> <PERSON> Tanaka </PERSON> was found guilty in 1983 of accepting bribes from the <ORGANIZATION> Lockheed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, but he remained an important force in Japanese politics until he suffered a stroke in 1985. <PERSON> Takeshita </PERSON>'s faction within the ruling party is made up mainly of former <PERSON> Tanaka </PERSON> followers.
